   "source": [
    "#  HEART DISEASE Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d1f269e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Problem Statement:\n",
    "Health is real wealth in the pandemic time we all realized the brute effects of covid-19 on\n",
    "all irrespective of any status. You are required to analyze this health and medical data for\n",
    "better future preparation.\n",
    "This database contains 76 attributes, but all published experiments refer to using a\n",
    "subset of 14 of them. In particular, the Cleveland database is the only one that has been\n",
    "used by ML researchers to this date. The “goal” field refers to the presence of heart\n",
    "disease in the patient. It is integer valued from 0 (no presence) to 4. Attribute\n",
    "Information:\n",
    "> 1. age> 2. sex> 3. chest pain type (4 values)> 4. resting blood pressure>\n",
    "5. serum cholesterol in mg/dl> 6. fasting blood sugar > 120 mg/dl> 7. resting\n",
    "electrocardiographic results (values 0,1,2)> 8. maximum heart rate achieved> 9.\n",
    "exercise induced angina> 10. oldpeak = ST depression induced by exercise relative to\n",
    "rest> 11. the slope of the peak exercise ST segment> 12. number of major vessels (0-3)\n",
    "colored by flourosopy> 13. thal: 3 = normal; 6 = fixed defect; 7 = reversible defect\n",
    "Find key metrics and factors and show the meaningful relationships between attributes.\n",
    "Do your own research and come up with your findings.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Analysis on Heart diseas.\n",
    "2. To predict whether the patient has heart disease or not. "
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis)\n",
    "\n",
    "Using Data Visualization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e0f9521b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1.age: Patients age in years\n",
    "\n",
    "2.sex : Female or male (1-Male,0-Female)\n",
    "\n",
    "3.cp :Chest pain ( 1- Typical Angina, 2-Atypical Angina,3-Non- anginal pain, 4-Asymptomatic)\n",
    "\n",
    "4.trestbp: Resting BloodPressure\n",
    "\n",
    "5.chol :Cholestrol \n",
    "\n",
    "6.fbs  : Fasting Blood Sugar( >120 mg/dl, 1-True, 0 - False)\n",
    "\n",
    "7.restecg : Resting electrocardiographic measurement (0 = normal, 1 = having ST-T wave abnormality, 2 = showing probable or definite left ventricular hypertrophy by Estes' criteria)\n",
    "\n",
    "8.thalach :The person's maximum heart rate achieved\n",
    "\n",
    "9.exang : Exercise induced angina (1 = yes; 0 = no)\n",
    "\n",
    "10.oldpeak: ST depression induced by exercise relative to rest ('ST' relates to positions on the ECG plot. See more here)\n",
    "\n",
    "11.slope  : the slope of the peak exercise ST segment (Value 1: upsloping, Value 2: flat, Value 3: downsloping)\n",
    "\n",
    "12.ca    :The number of major vessels (0-3)\n",
    "\n",
    "13.thal  : A blood disorder called thalassemia (3 = normal; 6 = fixed defect; 7 = reversable defect)\n",
    "\n",
    "14.target : Heart disease (0 = no, 1 = yes)\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Lets divide our data set and use  training dataset for model training, and test dataset is to eveluate model perfomance"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "id": "b5487b3e",

   "outputs": [

     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "X_train size: (227, 13), X_test size: (76, 13)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "x= heart.drop(columns= 'target')\n",
    "y= heart.target\n",
    "\n",
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test= train_test_split(x, y, test_size= 0.25, random_state=42)\n",
    "print('X_train size: {}, X_test size: {}'.format(x_train.shape, x_test.shape))"
   ]
  },

   "id": "39bb749a",

   "source": [

  },

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "scaler= StandardScaler()\n",
    "x_train_scaler= scaler.fit_transform(x_train)\n",
    "x_test_scaler= scaler.fit_transform(x_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9480dbde",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n",

    "y_pred_lr= lr_clf.predict(x_test_scaler)\n",
    "lr_clf.score(x_test_scaler,y_test)"
